cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark dataset, please cite both the dataset itself (using the metadata below) and the accompanying peer-reviewed paper (see 'preferred-citation')."
type: dataset
title: "SimilCode Benchmark: A Dual-Language Source-Code Similarity Dataset for the Evaluation of AI-Based Detectors"
abstract: >
  SimilCode Benchmark is a curated dataset of 120 short source-code snippets
  in C# and Java, organised into 60 test-case pairs per language across four
  ground-truth similarity categories (identical, functional, structural, and
  different) with fifteen reference groups per language. The dataset was
  designed and authored specifically to support the empirical evaluation of
  source-code similarity detection systems, and was used to benchmark four
  contemporary commercial large language models (Claude Opus 4.1, GPT-5,
  Gemini 2.5 Pro and DeepSeek-V3) as similarity analysts, with results
  published together with the dataset for reproducibility.
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-07-08"
license: CC-BY-4.0
